{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2016-10-17-ux-issues-with-authenticator-apps","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"kevinhakanson.com","author":"Kevin Hakanson"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"a077e6f7-57dd-5e55-a89c-f094f7dfeef3","excerpt":"I recently got a new personal iPhone and realized that none of my accounts stored in Google Authenticator were restored via the iCloud backup restore process…","html":"<p>I recently got a new personal iPhone and realized that none of my accounts stored in Google Authenticator were restored via the iCloud backup restore process.  I thought it might be time to switch authenticator apps to something like <a href=\"https://www.authy.com/app/\">Authy</a>, which supports encrypted backups and multiple devices (including desktop). </p>\n<p>So, I decided to try out some iOS Authenticator Apps using a stand-alone, in-browser, MFA demo website (<a href=\"https://daplie.github.io/browser-authenticator/\">https://daplie.github.io/browser-authenticator/</a>).  I was surprised by some fundamental UX issues I uncovered.</p>\n<p>To test, I generated a “secret” for fake Issuer (<code class=\"language-text\">Example Corporation</code>) and fake Account <code class=\"language-text\">firstname.lastname@corporation.example.com</code>.  Here’s the URI and QR code (feel free to steal my “secret”):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>otpauth://totp/Example%20Corporation:<a href=\"mailto:firstname.lastname@corporation.example.com\">firstname.lastname@corporation.example.com</a>?secret=XOJ4YXLNDHB7OLQFIIYW6E3NEXA5IEIE&#x26;issuer=Example%20Corporation&#x26;algorithm=SHA1&#x26;digits=6&#x26;period=30 </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 166px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5c703823188a0b4a7cb9c4f8d3835a28/e72ac/pastedImage_4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"TOTP QR code\"\n        title=\"TOTP QR code\"\n        src=\"/static/5c703823188a0b4a7cb9c4f8d3835a28/e72ac/pastedImage_4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5c703823188a0b4a7cb9c4f8d3835a28/12f09/pastedImage_4.png 148w,\n/static/5c703823188a0b4a7cb9c4f8d3835a28/e72ac/pastedImage_4.png 166w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 166px) 100vw, 166px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Now for the UX problems I found with these apps since my iOS device set to a larger font and I used longer than “normal” Issuer and Account values.</p>\n<p>First the <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/authy/id494168017?mt=8\">Authy iOS app</a>, which uses a small square box for the truncated <code class=\"language-text\">Example Corp...</code> issuer and even more truncated <code class=\"language-text\">firstname.lastname@...</code> account.  There is no excuse since Authy has so much white space to work with here.  Also, notice how unreadable that light grey text is on a white background.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 200px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8a9345888636dd331c9a14aa6c35d5a5/772e8/pastedImage_7.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 177.7027027027027%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Authy iOS app\"\n        title=\"Authy iOS app\"\n        src=\"/static/8a9345888636dd331c9a14aa6c35d5a5/772e8/pastedImage_7.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8a9345888636dd331c9a14aa6c35d5a5/12f09/pastedImage_7.png 148w,\n/static/8a9345888636dd331c9a14aa6c35d5a5/772e8/pastedImage_7.png 200w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Next was the <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/microsoft-authenticator/id983156458?mt=8\">Microsoft Authenticator iOS app</a>, which showed the full <code class=\"language-text\">Example Corporation</code> issuer, but truncated the <code class=\"language-text\">firstname.lastname@corporatio...</code> account.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 200px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/addcba2ec2ff3c4530c534b40413585e/772e8/pastedImage_10.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 177.7027027027027%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Microsoft Authenticator iOS app\"\n        title=\"Microsoft Authenticator iOS app\"\n        src=\"/static/addcba2ec2ff3c4530c534b40413585e/772e8/pastedImage_10.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/addcba2ec2ff3c4530c534b40413585e/12f09/pastedImage_10.png 148w,\n/static/addcba2ec2ff3c4530c534b40413585e/772e8/pastedImage_10.png 200w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Then was the <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/lastpass-authenticator/id1079110004?mt=8\">LastPass Authenticator iOS app</a>, which shows a larger and full <code class=\"language-text\">Example Corporation</code> issuer and a  truncated <code class=\"language-text\">firstname.lastname@corporation...</code> account.  However, they could have moved the countdown timer up to make room for the full issuer and avoided that grey text.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 200px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0d077cf0d1c7e5b05023241c903d1189/772e8/pastedImage_1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 177.7027027027027%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"LastPass Authenticator iOS app\"\n        title=\"LastPass Authenticator iOS app\"\n        src=\"/static/0d077cf0d1c7e5b05023241c903d1189/772e8/pastedImage_1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0d077cf0d1c7e5b05023241c903d1189/12f09/pastedImage_1.png 148w,\n/static/0d077cf0d1c7e5b05023241c903d1189/772e8/pastedImage_1.png 200w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Last was the <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/google-authenticator/id388497605?mt=8\">Google Authenticator iOS app</a>, which showed the most information with the full <code class=\"language-text\">Example Corporation</code> issuer and a less truncated <code class=\"language-text\">firstname.lastname@corporation.ex...</code> account.  However, why are there two entries for a single QR code camera scan?  Before you answer “user error,” I tried this twice and got the same result.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 200px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/95e5673c1e7363a7a73368edf6a1dc94/772e8/pastedImage_14.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 177.7027027027027%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Google Authenticator iOS app\"\n        title=\"Google Authenticator iOS app\"\n        src=\"/static/95e5673c1e7363a7a73368edf6a1dc94/772e8/pastedImage_14.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/95e5673c1e7363a7a73368edf6a1dc94/12f09/pastedImage_14.png 148w,\n/static/95e5673c1e7363a7a73368edf6a1dc94/772e8/pastedImage_14.png 200w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I was surprised they all had issues.  I even rotated the device for each app, hoping for more screen space, but no effect.</p>\n<p>I guess you get what you pay for.  It looks like the market could use an Authenticator app built by a UX team.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"UX Issues with Authenticator Apps","description":null,"date":"October 17, 2016","tags":["ux","mfa"],"canonical":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2016-10-17-ux-issues-with-authenticator-apps","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2016-10-11-i-have-people-skills"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["career"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2016-11-03-wolframalpha-and-pokmon-answers"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["random","nlp","pokemon"]}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2589769190","97908498"]}